{
  "analysis": "We are in /app/src with no visible output yet. The task requires enabling Hydra features without modifying existing Python scripts or base configs. We need to: 1) pip install the hydra-submitit-launcher plugin from the v1.3.0 release of facebookresearch/hydra's plugins/hydra_submitit_launcher subfolder; 2) add a debug mode config that reduces epochs to 1 and toggles debug to true, accessible via '+mode=debug'; 3) add a slurm configuration selectable via '-cn=slurm' that leaves the base job config unchanged while configuring the Hydra submitit SlurmLauncher with specified fields. To do this correctly, we must inspect the current repo layout (main.py and existing config directories) to place new YAML files at the correct path and use the correct config_name and group structure.",
  "plan": "1) Inspect /app/src contents to find main.py and any existing Hydra config directories/files (e.g., conf/, configs/, etc.), and view main.py to understand config_path/config_name. 2) Search for existing YAML configs to identify the base configuration keys and their location so we can create compatible new configs. 3) Install the hydra-submitit-launcher plugin directly from the GitHub v1.3.0 tag using pip with subdirectory installation. Optionally verify installation and that hydra-plugins entry points are registered. 4) Create a new config group 'mode' with a 'debug.yaml' that sets debug=true and train.max_num_epochs=1, leaving other fields intact. This will allow '+mode=debug' composition. 5) Create a new config named 'slurm.yaml' (matching whatever config_name convention main.py uses or the default) that composes the base job config (via defaults) and sets hydra.launcher with _target_ hydra_plugins.hydra_submitit_launcher.submitit_launcher.SlurmLauncher, additional_parameters.wckey: '' and srun_args including '--cpu-bind=none'. Ensure it does not alter job fields so '--cfg job' prints unchanged values. 6) If necessary, add a hydra search path config or package structure so Hydra finds the new configs. 7) Test the required commands: python /app/src/main.py +mode=debug --cfg job; python /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg job; python /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg hydra. Adjust file paths if needed based on main.py's config_path.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la /app/src\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 --version\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pip3 --version\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /app/src/main.py\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find /app -maxdepth 3 -type d -name 'conf' -o -type d -name 'configs' -o -type d -name 'config' -print\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find /app -maxdepth 3 -type f -name '*.yaml' -print\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pip3 install --no-cache-dir \"git+https://github.com/facebookresearch/hydra@v1.3.0#subdirectory=plugins/hydra_submitit_launcher\"\n",
      "duration": 20.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 -c \"import pkgutil; import hydra_plugins; import sys; print('submitit_launcher' in [m.name for m in pkgutil.iter_modules(hydra_plugins.__path__)])\"\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /app/src/conf/mode\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "printf \"debug: true\\ntrain:\\n  max_num_epochs: 1\\n\" > /app/src/conf/mode/debug.yaml\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /app/src/conf/hydra\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/src/conf/slurm.yaml << 'EOF'\n# Compose base job config via defaults; assumes base config_name is 'config' or 'default'.\n# We will not change base job fields here.\n# If main.py uses a different config_name, adjust via testing.\n# This file primarily sets the Hydra launcher for SLURM.\n\ndefaults:\n  - override hydra/launcher: submitit_slurm\n\n# Do not alter job keys; rely on base config for notes/debug/train.\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/src/conf/hydra/launcher/submitit_slurm.yaml << 'EOF'\n# Hydra Submitit Slurm launcher configuration\n_target_: hydra_plugins.hydra_submitit_launcher.submitit_launcher.SlurmLauncher\n# Minimal settings necessary for the cluster\nsubmitit_folder: ${hydra.runtime.output_dir}/.submitit/%j\ntimeout_min: 60\nadditional_parameters:\n  wckey: ''\nsrun_args:\n  - --cpu-bind=none\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py +mode=debug --cfg job\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg job\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg hydra\n",
