{
  "analysis": "We inspected the project. main.py uses Hydra with config_path='config' and config_name='config', and the base config is at /app/src/config/config.yaml. We installed the hydra-submitit-launcher plugin from the Hydra repo v1.3.0 (built as 1.3.0.dev0). Our earlier configs were mistakenly created under /app/src/conf, which is not on Hydra's search path. As a result, '+mode=debug' added a free parameter 'mode: debug' but did not change debug or epochs. Also, the SLURM config slurm.yaml must live under /app/src/config (since -cn=slurm seeks /app/src/config/slurm.yaml). We also need to provide a hydra/launcher/submitit_slurm.yaml under the same config path to configure the SlurmLauncher correctly. Finally, slurm.yaml should include the base application config and override the hydra launcher, so that '--cfg job' remains identical to the base job config.",
  "plan": "- View the base config to confirm keys. - Create the debug mode in the correct location: /app/src/config/mode/debug.yaml overriding debug=true and train.max_num_epochs=1. - Create the Hydra launcher override at /app/src/config/hydra/launcher/submitit_slurm.yaml with the required _target_, additional_parameters.wckey, and srun_args including --cpu-bind=none. - Create /app/src/config/slurm.yaml that composes the base primary config and overrides hydra/launcher to submitit_slurm, ensuring job keys remain as in base. - Test the three required commands to validate outputs.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,200p' /app/src/config/config.yaml\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /app/src/config/mode\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "printf \"debug: true\\ntrain:\\n  max_num_epochs: 1\\n\" > /app/src/config/mode/debug.yaml\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /app/src/config/hydra/launcher\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/src/config/hydra/launcher/submitit_slurm.yaml << 'EOF'\n_target_: hydra_plugins.hydra_submitit_launcher.submitit_launcher.SlurmLauncher\n# folder where submitit will store logs and submission info\nsubmitit_folder: ${hydra.runtime.output_dir}/.submitit/%j\n# example timeout; adjust as needed for cluster\ntimeout_min: 60\nadditional_parameters:\n  wckey: ''\nsrun_args:\n  - --cpu-bind=none\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/src/config/slurm.yaml << 'EOF'\n# Compose the base primary config and override the launcher to use Submitit Slurm\ndefaults:\n  - config            # include base primary config.yaml\n  - override hydra/launcher: submitit_slurm\n  - _self_\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py +mode=debug --cfg job\n",
      "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg job\n",
      "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py -cn=slurm --cfg hydra\n",
      "duration": 1.5
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "We confirmed the project structure: Hydra uses config_path='config' and config_name='config'. The base YAML at /app/src/config/config.yaml has the expected keys. We successfully installed the hydra-submitit-launcher from the specified GitHub subdirectory and configured a Slurm launcher via /app/src/config/hydra/launcher/submitit_slurm.yaml. The slurm config at /app/src/config/slurm.yaml composes the base config and overrides the launcher; tests show the hydra config includes the SlurmLauncher with the required additional_parameters.wckey='' and srun_args '--cpu-bind=none'. However, the debug feature is not yet behaving as required because '+mode=debug' currently adds a nested 'mode' section rather than overriding root keys. We need to adjust the debug config to compose into the global namespace.",
  "plan": "Update /app/src/config/mode/debug.yaml to use 'package: _global_' so that composing '+mode=debug' overrides the root-level values (debug=true and train.max_num_epochs=1). Then rerun the debug test command to verify the printed output matches the requirement.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/src/config/mode/debug.yaml << 'EOF'\npackage: _global_\ndebug: true\ntrain:\n  max_num_epochs: 1\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /app/src/main.py +mode=debug --cfg job\n",
      "duration": 1.5
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": true
}

