  "analysis": "We installed the hydra-submitit-launcher plugin and set up the SLURM launcher correctly. The slurm configuration prints the base job config unchanged and shows the launcher with the required _target_, additional_parameters.wckey, and srun_args. The remaining issue is the debug mode: using '+mode=debug' currently nests the debug overrides under a 'mode' node. To make '+mode=debug' override the root-level keys, we should make the 'mode/debug.yaml' file include defaults that select other groups which affect the root: one to override train.max_num_epochs and one to set debug=true at the global level.",
  "plan": "Create two new config groups: 'train/debug.yaml' to override train.max_num_epochs, and 'debug_flag/true.yaml' to set debug=true with package: _global_. Then update 'mode/debug.yaml' to only contain a defaults list including these two groups, so that selecting '+mode=debug' composes them into the root config. Finally, test the required debug command to confirm it prints the expected output.",
  "commands": [
